<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>tooling on @atamanroman - My Personal Space - IT, Development, Software Architecture and Things I Care About</title><link>https://www.atamanroman.dev/tags/tooling/</link><description>Recent content in tooling on @atamanroman - My Personal Space - IT, Development, Software Architecture and Things I Care About</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 10 Aug 2020 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.atamanroman.dev/tags/tooling/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Change Your Git User Depending on the Current Directory with Conditional Includes</title><link>https://www.atamanroman.dev/links/change-git-user-depending-current-directory-conditional-include/</link><pubDate>Mon, 10 Aug 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.atamanroman.dev/links/change-git-user-depending-current-directory-conditional-include/</guid><description>&lt;p>Git 2.13+ introduced &lt;a href="https://git-scm.com/docs/git-config#_conditional_includes">&lt;em>Conditional Includes&lt;/em>&lt;/a> which allow to set the Git user name depending on the Git repo directory (and much more):&lt;/p>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">3
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">4
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span class="o">[&lt;/span>includeIf &lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;gitdir:~/code/&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">]&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="nv">path&lt;/span> &lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span> .gitconfig-personal
&lt;span class="o">[&lt;/span>includeIf &lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;gitdir:~/code/work/&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">]&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="nv">path&lt;/span> &lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span> .gitconfig-work
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>â€” Example from &lt;!-- raw HTML omitted -->&lt;a href="https://www.motowilliams.com/conditional-includes-for-git-config">Eric William&lt;/a>&lt;!-- raw HTML omitted -->&lt;/p>
